cover\n| type = single\n| cover = Ava Max Salt Original Cover.jpg\n| border = yes\n| caption = Original cover\n}}\n{{External music video|{{YouTube|2EfE0vhxt1o|\"Salt\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Salt'''\" is a song by American singer [[Ava Max]], released as a single on December 12, 2019 through [[Atlantic Records]], despite having already been released to [[YouTube]] and [[SoundCloud]] in July 2018.<ref name=\"Idolator\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.idolator.com/7904225/ava-max-is-all-cried-out-feeling-fabulous-on-fierce-new-single-salt|title=Ava Max Is All Cried Out & Feeling Fabulous On Fierce New Single Salt|last=Nied|first=Mike|website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|date=December 12, 2019|access-date=December 22, 2019}}</ref> The song has also been regarded as a \"fan favorite\".<ref name=\"MTV Salt\"/><ref name=\"Idolator\"/><ref name=\"BillboardRelease\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8546157/ava-max-salt-listen|title=Ava Max Finally Drops Fan Favorite Song 'Salt'|last=Aniftos|first=Rania|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=December 12, 2019|access-date=December 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Background and composition==\n\"Salt\" was initially released on several streaming platforms in July 2018 as a promotional single, which included [[YouTube]] and [[SoundCloud]].<ref name=\"MTV Salt\"/> On December 5, 2019, Max revealed the song's release date on social media,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/AvaMax/status/1202724362417139713|title=Your wish is my command \u2763\ufe0f\ud83d\ude80|via=[[Twitter]]|date=December 5, 2019|access-date=December 26, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191206064554/https://twitter.com/AvaMax/status/1202724362417139713|archive-date=December 6, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> which was subsequently released on all streaming platforms on December 12, 2019.<ref name=\"BillboardRelease\"/>\n\nIt is described as a song filled with \"pumping disco beats from the seventies and eighties\", blended with Max's \"vocal inflexions\".<ref name=\"MusicTalkers\">{{cite web|url=https://musictalkers.com/latest-news/6232-ava-max-gets-down-to-disco-in-%E2%80%98salt%E2%80%99|title=Ava Max Gets Down To Disco In 'Salt'|last=Das|first=Shaoni|website=Music Talkers|date=December 19, 2019|access-date=January 12, 2020}}</ref> The violin is heard in the introduction, while [[Wonder Woman]] and [[Marilyn Monroe]] are lyrically mentioned throughout the song.<ref name=\"MusicTalkers\"/> It is based on [[Time signature|{{Time signature|4|4}} common time]], the tempo is 128 [[Tempo|bpm]] and is played in the [[Key (music)|key]] of [[D-sharp minor]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tunebat.com/Info/Salt-Ava-Max/7vgv8KZBSo0TPzyIWG9yzV|title=Key & BPM for Salt by Ava Max - Tunebat|publisher=Tunebat|access-date=December 27, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\nRania Aniftos of ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' described the song as an \"upbeat, sassy track about having fun after a sad spell\",<ref name=\"BillboardRelease\"/> while Madeline Roth of [[MTV News]] felt that it was \"[[dance-pop]] blissfulness\".<ref name=\"MTV Salt\"/> Shaoni Das of ''Music Talkers'' stated that the song is an \"exhilarating dance number, awash in pools of glitter, glamour, and confidence\".<ref name=\"MusicTalkers\"/>\n\n==Track listing==\n*'''Digital download'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/salt-single/1490153026|title=Salt \u2013 Single|website=[[iTunes Store]]|access-date=December 26, 2019}}</ref>\n#\"Salt\" \u2013 3:00\n\n*'''Digital download \u2013 acoustic'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/salt-acoustic-single/1506185126|title=Salt (Acoustic) \u2013 Single|website=[[Apple Music]]|access-date=April 11, 2020}}</ref>\n#\"Salt (Acoustic)\" \u2013 3:10\n\n* '''Streaming'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://open.spotify.com/album/6KPJTxKFCpuzrwyJGcURqK|title=Salt|website=[[Spotify]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191226032116/https://open.spotify.com/album/6KPJTxKFCpuzrwyJGcURqK|archive-date=December 26, 2019|access-date=December 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\n# \"Salt\" \u2013 3:00\n# \"[[Torn (Ava Max song)|Torn]]\" \u2013 3:18\n# \"Freaking Me Out\" \u2013 3:12\n\n==Credits and personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref name=\"Tidal\"/>\n\n* [[Ava Max|Amanda Ava Koci]] \u2013 vocals, songwriting\n* [[Cirkut (record producer)|Henry Walter]] \u2013 songwriting, production, mixing\n* [[Autumn Rowe]] \u2013 songwriting\n* [[Madison Love]] \u2013 songwriting\n* [[Coco Morier|Nicole Morier]] \u2013 songwriting\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2019\u20132020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{single chart|Austria|9|artist=Ava Max|song=Salt|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 9, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|CIS|4|artist=Ava Max|song=Salt|songid=98326|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 24, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Croatia ([[Croatian Radiotelevision|HRT]])<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://radio.hrt.hr/clanak/arc-100-datum-6-travnja-2020/226648/|title=Croatia ARC TOP 100|publisher=HRT|access-date=April 7, 2020}}</ref>\n| 56\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Denmark ([[Tracklisten]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hitlisten.nu/default.asp?w=10&y=2020&list=t40|title=Track Top-40 Uge 10, 2020|publisher=[[Hitlisten]]|accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref>\n| 25\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Euro Digital Songs]] (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/euro-digital-song-sales|title=Euro Digital Song Sales Chart (The week of April 11, 2020)|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 10, 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200410180005/https://www.billboard.com/charts/euro-digital-song-sales|archivedate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n| 15\n|-\n{{single chart|Finland|6|artist=Ava Max|song=Salt|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 8, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| France ([[Syndicat National d