ngland\n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n|  years1 =   1929\u20131932  \n| years2 =   \n|  clubs1 =   [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]]  \n| clubs2 =   [[Luton Town F.C.|Luton Town]]\n| caps1 =    26   \n| caps2 =  \n| goals1 =  8  \n| goals2 = \n}}\n'''George Crownshaw''' (17 April 1908 \u2013 October 1992) was a professional [[association football|footballer]] who played for [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] & [[Luton Town F.C.|Luton Town]]. He was born in [[Sheffield]], [[South Yorkshire]].\n\n==References==\n*{{cite book|title=99 Years and Counting: Stats and Stories|author=Ian Thomas|author2=Owen Thomas|author3=Alan Hodgson|author4=John Ward|year=2007|publisher=Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|isbn=095572810X}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Crownshaw, George}}\n[[Category:1908 births]]\n[[Category:1992 deaths]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Sheffield]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Huddersfield Town A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Luton Town F.C. players]]\n\n\n{{England-footy-midfielder-1900s-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Red Director", "label": "safe", "comment": "Adding localshort description: \"English footballer\", overriding Wikidata description \"English footballer\" (Shortdesc helper)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/George_Crownshaw"}
